- Use `dotnet new webapi` to create a new ASP.NET Core Web API project.
- Update `Program.cs` for authentication and authorization:
  ```csharp
  builder.Services.AddAuthentication(JwtBearerDefaults.AuthenticationScheme)
      .AddJwtBearer(options =>
      {
          options.TokenValidationParameters = new TokenValidationParameters
          {
              ValidateIssuer = true,
              ValidateAudience = true,
              ValidateLifetime = true,
              ValidateIssuerSigningKey = true,
              ValidIssuer = "your_issuer",
              ValidAudience = "your_audience",
              IssuerSigningKey = new SymmetricSecurityKey(Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes("your_secret_key"))
          };
      });

  builder.Services.AddAuthorization();
  ```
- Configure `appsettings.json` for JWT settings:
  ```json
  {
    "Jwt": {
      "Issuer": "your_issuer",
      "Audience": "your_audience",
      "Key": "your_secret_key"
    }
  }
  ```
- Use `[Authorize]` attribute on controllers or actions to secure them.
- Implement an API Gateway using YARP for centralized authentication and routing.
- Ensure HTTPS is enabled by configuring `appsettings.json`:
  ```json
  {
    "Kestrel": {
      "Endpoints": {
        "Http": {
          "Url": "http://localhost:5000"
        },
        "Https": {
          "Url": "https://localhost:5001",
          "Certificate": {
            "Path": "path_to_certificate.pfx",
            "Password": "certificate_password"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  ```
- Use `dotnet dev-certs https --trust` to trust the development certificate.
- Regularly update dependencies and .NET Core SDK to benefit from security patches.
